import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data, hue='series', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Series', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of rate?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='month', y='count', data=data, ci=None, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count by month?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='year', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate by year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
